GOVERNMENT OF INDIA
CABINET SECRETARIAT
(Department of Cabinet Affairs)
IMMEDIATE
New Delhi, the 25th January 1966.
A copy of the Order of the President dated January 24,
1966, regarding the functions assigned to Shri Dinesh Singh,
in addition to his functions as Minister of State in the
Ministry of External Affairs, is circulated to the Members
of the Council of Ministers, for information.

(D.P. Chopra)

Cabinet.

CONFIDENTIAL
Rashtrapati Bhavan,
New Delhi,
sll
January 24, 1966.
ORDER
I, Sarvepalli Radhakrishnan, President of India,
on the advice of the Prime Minister, am pleased to
direct that Shri Dinesh Singh, Minister of State in
the Ministry of External Affairs shall perform such
functions as may be assigned by the Prime Minister
in addition to his functions as Minister of State in
the Ministry of External Affairs.
S. Radhakrishnan
President of India.
